From 12de1fb68f156942433165055481fa80cc859cd9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aneesh Pradhan <aneeshpradhan@acm.org>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 01:43:02 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] media: i2c: add Samsung S5K4H8 image sensor driver

Add a V4L2 sub-device driver for the Samsung S5K4H8 8MP raw sensor
(MIPI CSI-2, 4-lane, 280 MHz link, 24 MHz MCLK). Register programming
sequences are adapted from the Rockchip vendor driver; register I/O
uses mainline v4l2-cci.

The driver uses the modern V4L2 subdev active-state API
(init_state, enable_streams / disable_streams, v4l2_subdev_init_finalize).

Supported modes:
  - 3264x2448 SGRBG10 @ ~25 fps
  - 1632x1224 SGRBG10 2x2 binning @ ~30 fps

Controls: exposure, analogue gain, VBLANK, LINK_FREQ, PIXEL_RATE,
fwnode Location/Rotation. Selection targets expose crop and native size.

Tested on Motorola Moto E4 (perry / MSM8917) with mainline CAMSS and
libcamera (~24 fps full-resolution capture).

Signed-off-by: Aneesh Pradhan <aneeshpradhan@acm.org>
